FBIS3-19146 "drweu049l?_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-049 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 SPAIN Government To Send 200 Extra Troops to Bosnia LD1203110894 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 0900 GMT 12 Mar 94 LD1203110894 Madrid RNE International Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] In response to the request from the United Nations to increase the number of soldiers in the conflict zone, Spain will send to Bosnia-Herzegovina about 200 more blue helmets, who will join the Spanish UN battalion next week. In all, the new Spanish contribution will comprise around 200 men, who will be joining the 1,200 Spanish blue helmets stationed in the Mostar area. It is expected that they will be able to travel to the former Yugoslavia during the course of next week. According to an official spokesman, a radar detection unit, which locates mortar and heavy weapon trajectories, will be sent. The unit will comprise six vehicles and 25 men, who will have the task of monitoring and consolidating the cease-fire in the city of Mostar, which is considered vital for the security of the population.
